I am an dedicated CFA customer and I ALWAYS associate great quality food and great service with the brand. However, this CFA seems to have missed the memo. This was my first time going to the Westshore location and it will definitely be my last! The employees were RUDE, we were ignored for a while before they even acknowledged that we were WAITING IN LINE. An off the clock employee kept jumping in front of us and interrupting the young man while taking our order to get his stuff and with ridiculous complaints. And the food! That was the first time I've EVER had a CFA meal and not finish it. I'm usually licking the crumbs of the fry carton, but I could barely keep this meal down. Our fries were a limp, greasy mess with a bad aftertaste, our bread was stale and our pickles had big holes in them. Who the heck has fricking HOLES in ALL of the pickles????!!!! Overall, the food quality and the customer service were both enough to leave me feel nauseous. Won't ever return.

One of the female cashiers just stood picking her nails, not making eye contact as my mother was trying to ask her a question about the menu, she also spoke to my mother so rudely! I will not be returning to this Chic fil a. Word of advice: Hire new employees!!
